**BEM (Block Element Modifier):**

**What BEM Stands For:**
- **B** - Block (Independent component)
- **E** - Element (Part of a block)
- **M** - Modifier (Variation of block/element)

**What BEM Does:**
- **Naming Convention:** Standardized CSS class naming
- **Component Structure:** Clear hierarchy and relationships
- **Maintainability:** Easy to understand and modify
- **Scalability:** Works well in large projects
- **Specificity:** Avoids specificity wars

**Complete BEM Structure:**

**1. Block:**
- Independent, reusable component
- **Naming:** `block-name`
- **Example:** `button`, `card`, `header`

**2. Element:**
- Part of a block, cannot exist alone
- **Naming:** `block-name__element-name`
- **Example:** `button__text`, `card__title`, `header__logo`

**3. Modifier:**
- Variation of block or element
- **Naming:** `block-name--modifier-name` or `block-name__element-name--modifier-name`
- **Example:** `button--primary`, `card--large`, `button__text--bold`

**BEM Examples:**

**HTML Structure:**
```html
<div class="card card--large">
    <h2 class="card__title">Card Title</h2>
    <p class="card__content">Card content</p>
    <button class="card__button card__button--primary">Click me</button>
</div>
```

**CSS Structure:**
```css
/* Block */
.card {
    background: white;
    border-radius: 8px;
    padding: 20px;
}

/* Element */
.card__title {
    font-size: 24px;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
}

.card__content {
    color: #666;
    line-height: 1.5;
}

.card__button {
    background: #ccc;
    border: none;
    padding: 10px 20px;
}

/* Modifier */
.card--large {
    padding: 40px;
}

.card__button--primary {
    background: #007bff;
    color: white;
}
```

**BEM Benefits:**
- **Clear Structure:** Easy to understand component hierarchy
- **No Specificity Issues:** Flat CSS structure
- **Reusable:** Components can be easily reused
- **Maintainable:** Easy to find and modify styles
- **Team Friendly:** Consistent naming across team

**CSS Modules:**

**What CSS Modules Are:**
A CSS file in which all class names and animation names are scoped locally by default, preventing style conflicts.

**How CSS Modules Work:**
- **Local Scope:** Class names are automatically scoped to the component
- **Unique Names:** Generates unique class names to avoid conflicts
- **Import/Export:** CSS is imported as JavaScript objects
- **Build Process:** Transforms CSS during build time

**Complete CSS Modules Features:**

**1. Local Scope:**
- Class names are scoped to the component
- No global namespace pollution
- Automatic unique naming

**2. Import/Export:**
- Import CSS as JavaScript objects
- Export class names for use in components
- Type-safe class name access

**3. Composition:**
- Combine multiple classes
- Extend existing styles
- Reuse common patterns

**4. Build Integration:**
- Works with Webpack, Vite, Parcel
- Automatic transformation
- Development and production builds

**CSS Modules Examples:**

**CSS File (Button.module.css):**
```css
.button {
    background: #007bff;
    color: white;
    padding: 10px 20px;
    border: none;
    border-radius: 4px;
}

.button:hover {
    background: #0056b3;
}

.button--large {
    padding: 15px 30px;
    font-size: 18px;
}
```

**JavaScript/React Usage:**
```javascript
import styles from './Button.module.css';

function Button({ children, large }) {
    return (
        <button 
            className={`${styles.button} ${large ? styles['button--large'] : ''}`}
        >
            {children}
        </button>
    );
}
```

**Generated CSS:**
```css
.Button_button__2x3kl {
    background: #007bff;
    color: white;
    padding: 10px 20px;
    border: none;
    border-radius: 4px;
}

.Button_button--large__1a2b3c {
    padding: 15px 30px;
    font-size: 18px;
}
```

**CSS Modules Benefits:**
- **No Conflicts:** Scoped styles prevent naming conflicts
- **Maintainable:** Clear component boundaries
- **Type Safe:** IDE support for class names
- **Performance:** Optimized CSS output
- **Team Friendly:** No naming conventions needed

**SCSS (Sass):**

**What SCSS Is:**
SCSS (Sassy CSS) is a CSS preprocessor that extends CSS with variables, nesting, mixins, functions, and other programming features.

**What SCSS Does:**
- **Variables:** Store values for reuse
- **Nesting:** Write nested CSS rules
- **Mixins:** Reusable code blocks
- **Functions:** Perform calculations
- **Imports:** Split CSS into multiple files
- **Inheritance:** Extend existing styles

**Complete SCSS Features:**

**1. Variables:**
```scss
$primary-color: #007bff;
$font-size: 16px;
$border-radius: 4px;

.button {
    background: $primary-color;
    font-size: $font-size;
    border-radius: $border-radius;
}
```

**2. Nesting:**
```scss
.navbar {
    background: #333;
    padding: 1rem;

    .nav-item {
        color: white;
        margin: 0 1rem;

        &:hover {
            color: #007bff;
        }

        &.active {
            font-weight: bold;
        }
    }
}
```

**3. Mixins:**
```scss
@mixin button-style($bg-color, $text-color: white) {
    background: $bg-color;
    color: $text-color;
    padding: 10px 20px;
    border: none;
    border-radius: 4px;
    cursor: pointer;
}

.primary-button {
    @include button-style(#007bff);
}

.secondary-button {
    @include button-style(#6c757d);
}
```

**4. Functions:**
```scss
@function calculate-rem($px) {
    @return $px / 16px * 1rem;
}

.text {
    font-size: calculate-rem(18px); // 1.125rem
}
```

**5. Imports:**
```scss
@import 'variables';
@import 'mixins';
@import 'components/button';
@import 'components/card';
```

**6. Inheritance:**
```scss
%button-base {
    padding: 10px 20px;
    border: none;
    border-radius: 4px;
    cursor: pointer;
}

.primary-button {
    @extend %button-base;
    background: #007bff;
    color: white;
}
```

**SCSS Benefits:**
- **DRY Principle:** Don't Repeat Yourself
- **Maintainable:** Easier to update styles
- **Organized:** Better code structure
- **Powerful:** Advanced CSS features
- **Compatible:** Compiles to regular CSS

**CSS-in-JS Libraries:**

**What CSS-in-JS Is:**
A styling approach where CSS is written in JavaScript, allowing for dynamic styling, component-scoped styles, and better integration with JavaScript frameworks.

**What CSS-in-JS Does:**
- **Component Scoping:** Styles are scoped to components
- **Dynamic Styling:** Styles can change based on props/state
- **JavaScript Integration:** Use JS variables and functions
- **No Global Conflicts:** Avoids CSS naming conflicts
- **Type Safety:** TypeScript support for styles

**Complete CSS-in-JS Libraries:**

**1. Styled Components:**
```javascript
import styled from 'styled-components';

const Button = styled.button`
    background: ${props => props.primary ? '#007bff' : '#6c757d'};
    color: white;
    padding: 10px 20px;
    border: none;
    border-radius: 4px;
    cursor: pointer;

    &:hover {
        opacity: 0.8;
    }
`;

// Usage
<Button primary>Primary Button</Button>
<Button>Secondary Button</Button>
```

**2. Emotion:**
```javascript
import { css } from '@emotion/react';

const buttonStyle = css`
    background: #007bff;
    color: white;
    padding: 10px 20px;
    border: none;
    border-radius: 4px;
    cursor: pointer;
`;

// Usage
<button css={buttonStyle}>Click me</button>
```

**3. JSS (JavaScript Style Sheets):**
```javascript
import { createUseStyles } from 'react-jss';

const useStyles = createUseStyles({
    button: {
        background: '#007bff',
        color: 'white',
        padding: '10px 20px',
        border: 'none',
        borderRadius: '4px',
        cursor: 'pointer'
    }
});

// Usage
function Button() {
    const classes = useStyles();
    return <button className={classes.button}>Click me</button>;
}
```

**4. Stitches:**
```javascript
import { styled } from '@stitches/react';

const Button = styled('button', {
    backgroundColor: '$blue500',
    color: 'white',
    padding: '$2 $4',
    border: 'none',
    borderRadius: '$2',
    cursor: 'pointer'
});
```

**5. Vanilla Extract:**
```javascript
// button.css.ts
import { style } from '@vanilla-extract/css';

export const button = style({
    backgroundColor: '#007bff',
    color: 'white',
    padding: '10px 20px',
    border: 'none',
    borderRadius: '4px',
    cursor: 'pointer'
});

// Usage
